title: 15-Year-Old Mom, 8-Month-Old Daughter Missing After Trip To Park
text:
15-Year-Old Mom, 8-Month-Old Daughter Missing After Trip To Park February 19, 2017 6:46 PM 
CORUNNA (WWJ) – Police are asking for help from the public in locating a missing teen mom and her young daughter. Renee Stapel, 15, and her daughter Rebecca. (Shiawasee County Dispatch) 
Renee Stapel, 15, and 8-month-old, Rebecca, have not been seen since Saturday around 4 p.m. when the young mom told family she was going to a park in Corunna with her daughter and would be back in 10 minutes. 
Corunna police tell WWJ that the FBI and Michigan State Police are involved in the investigation. 
Police in Shiawasee County describe Stapel as 5-foot tall and weighing 100 pounds. She has long brown hair and blue eyes. She was last seen wearing jeans and a pink Michigan sweatshirt, and gray cowboy boots. 
The pair did not return and Stapel did not have baby supplies with her when she left — according to police the baby was ill when Stapel left the home. 
If you have any information or know the whereabouts of Renee Stapel or Rebbeca, you are asked to contact Corunna police.
